class WeatherSimulator {
    private boolean isRainy;
    private boolean isWeekend;

    public WeatherSimulator() {
        this.isRainy = Math.random() < 0.4;
        this.isWeekend = Math.random() < 0.3;
    }

    public boolean decideToGoOut() {
        return isWeekend && !isRainy;
    }

    public boolean adjustRainProbability(double intervention) {
        isRainy = Math.random() < intervention;
        return isRainy;
    }

    public boolean isItWeekend() {
        return isWeekend;
    }
}
",

If we observe that the simulator did not decide to go out after intervention that set rain probability to 0%, can we conclude it was not the weekend?
